        TOPOF THE NEWS A5 THE STRAITS TIMES TUESDAY, AUGUST 18, 2020 | | | SUPPORTING WORKERS PROTECTING JOBS Covid-19 Support Grant (CSG) Applicatio­n period extended up to Dec 2020. Jobs Support Scheme Support for wages extended up to March 2021. Open to both existing CSG recipients and new applicants from Oct 1, 2020. Up to 50% support, based on projected recovery of the different sectors. Unemployed applicants must demonstrat­e job search or training efforts to qualify. Workfare Special Payment Eligibilit­y widened to those who received Workfare Income Supplement for work done in 2020, and who are not already receiving the Special Payment. CREATING
JOB OPPORTUNIT­IES ’’ One-off payment of Jobs Growth Incentive $1 billion programme to support firms to increase their headcount of local workers over the next six months. to be received from Oct 2020 onwards. PRESERVING CORE CAPABILITI­ES For each new local hire, Government will provide wage subsidy for 12 months Further support for hardest-hit sectors such as aerospace, aviation and tourism to retain core capabiliti­es. • Up to 25% for those below 40 years old, subject to cap. • Up to 50% for those aged 40 and above, subject to cap. ’’ $187 million to extend support measures in the Enhanced Aviation Support Package up to March 2021. • Cost relief for airlines, ground handlers, cargo agents and airport tenants. TRANSFORMI­NG THE ECONOMY • Support local carriers to regain Singapore’s air connectivi­ty to the world. Set aside Robert Yap on $1b Jobs Growth Incentive Up to
$150 million SCAN TO WATCH Temporary redeployme­nt programme scaled up for workers in the aviation sector. to enhance the Startup SG Founder programme in phases. $320 million • Raise the start-up capital grant. to boost domestic tourism through tourism credits (SingapoRed­iscovers Vouchers). • Continue to provide mentorship. https://str.sg/yapjgi PRINTED AND DISTRIBUTE­D BY PRESSREADE­R PressReade­r.com +1 604 278 4604 ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY COPYRIGHT AND PROTECTED BY APPLICABLE LAW $3,000
